From 67ed5fe913bd92c0949f9c2be887bab24885400a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Jake Teton-Landis <just.1.jake@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 2 Jul 2026 23:39:39 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 04/25] Slim the external-runtime surface to the token protocol
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Remove the v1 lane exports (unstable_getCurrentUpdateLane,
unstable_isTransitionLane, unstable_lanesInclude) from every entry fork and
the isomorphic registry, plus the dead batchesForLanes provider method —
all superseded by batch tokens; nothing consumed them.

Deduplicate the runtime accessor: ReactFiberExternalRuntime now exports one
typed getExternalRuntime() reusing the real ExternalRuntime type, replacing
the hand-copied ExternalRuntimeLike and the batch registry's second untyped
accessor. registerExternalRuntimeProvider is properly typed. Module docs
rewritten from lane vocabulary to token vocabulary.

Flow (dom-node) clean; all react-signals tests pass against the rebuild.
